Written evidence submitted [bold]by Catherine Turner OBE BSc (Hons)[bold] (FFS025)[bold]Author and [bold]Declaration of Interests[bold]  [bold]I graduated with a BSc (Hons) degree in Biomedical Sciences, and
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]have been a forensic scientist for over twenty four years. Over the last ten years I have specialised in the area of historic case reviews
[normal] (cold cases)
[normal], and was the National Lead in case reviews for the Forensic Science Service prior to its closure.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]In this field, I am co-author of the Home Office ‘Good Practice Guide: Cold Case Reviews of Rape and Serious Sexual Assault’, published in 2005. In May 2012 I joined LGC Forensics as a specialist in forensic case reviews. 
[normal]I 
[normal]was awarded an OBE for 
[normal]my work within forensic science
[normal] in the 
[normal]Queen’s 
[normal]New Years Honours list
[normal] 2013
[normal], and ha
[normal]ve
[normal] received twelve Commendations from within the Criminal Justice System - eight Crown Court Commendations and four Police Commendations. 
[normal]I
[normal] was also part of the Police/forensic/CPS team nominated for the South Yorkshire Justice Awards 2009.
